# WordPress Coding Standards

## Namespace
- Root: KomboManager
- Sub: KomboManager\Admin, KomboManager\Frontend, KomboManager\Core, KomboManager\Api
- Every class file must declare namespace

## Naming
- Constants: KM_VERSION, KM_DIR, KM_URL, KM_FILE
- Functions (only when hooks require it): km_function_name()
- Classes: PascalCase, one class per file
- Custom hooks: kombo_manager_{hook_name}

## Hook registration
- All add_action / add_filter inside __construct() or register_hooks() only
- Never at file scope (top level)

## Options / meta / transients
- Options API keys: km_{key}
- User meta keys: km_{key}
- Transients: km_transient_{key}

## Enqueue
- Scripts/styles via wp_enqueue_scripts or admin_enqueue_scripts
- Handle prefix: km-{handle}
- Never inline <script> or <style> tags from PHP

## Translation
- All user-facing strings: __('string', 'kombo-manager') or _e()
- No hardcoded Serbian strings in PHP output